text:
Nancy Nordstrom
Nancy Nordstrom was a classmate of Dale Cooper at the Germantown Friends School.
Nancy was in the tenth grade in 1969 and played goaltender for the school's field hockey team. She began dating new student Anne Sweeny, prompting Cooper – who was infatuated with Anne – to blow up Nancy's mailbox.
Before moving away with her family, Anne purchased a Willa Cather book for Nancy as a parting gift.
